Usage: gskill store <command> [flags]

Manage the global content store.

Examples:

    gskill store status
    gskill store gc --apply
    gskill store repair sha256:abc123…

Flags:
  -h, --help              Show context-sensitive help.
      --json              Emit machine-readable JSON on stdout.
      --quiet             Suppress diagnostics on stderr.
      --no-interactive    Disable prompts and colored output.
      --yes               Assume yes for confirmation prompts.
      --offline           Operate without network access.
      --no-cache          Bypass the content cache.
      --dry-run           Report actions without applying them.
      --config=STRING     Path to a config file.
  -v, --verbose           Enable verbose diagnostics.
  -C, --dir=STRING        Run as if gskill started in this directory.

MORE
  store status
    Summarize the global store.

  store list
    List stored objects and their users.

  store inspect <hash>
    Show one object's integrity, origins, and users.

  store verify
    Verify every global store object's integrity.

  store repair <hash>
    Restore a corrupted object from its recorded origin.

  store gc [flags]
    Report (default) or delete unused store objects.

  store pin <hash>
    Exempt an object from garbage collection.

  store unpin <hash>
    Remove an object's GC exemption.

  store pins
    List pinned objects.
